The story of how Bosasa dished out millions to those more equal than others to buy their favour. Our columnist Vusi Nzapheza weighs in on bribery scandal exposed in the state capture commission In the Kingdom of the Butternut, life was good. The Bosasanosaurus were the kings of the jungle, doling out cash to extend the life of their rotten empire. They made the rules and scavenged with impunity. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD.